# Scanner-engine bundle source (M3-W2).
#
# Semgrep CE is the MVP SAST engine (LGPL-2.1 engine; run against a VENDORED,
# content-hashed rule bundle on a local path — never floating registry aliases;
# CLAUDE.md §3). Like PyRIT (requirements-redteam.in), it is a heavy dependency
# with a large transitive tree, so it is deliberately kept OUT of the base uv.lock
# and installed only into the dedicated `scanners` image stage. Rationale: the
# block-on-High SCA gate runs osv-scanner against uv.lock — keeping semgrep out of
# uv.lock isolates its transitive-dependency blast radius from the base image and
# the base SCA/Trivy gates (SECURITY_DEVELOPMENT_PLAN §7).
#
# Pinned exact to the same version the CI self-scan already vets
# (.github/workflows/security.yml uses semgrep@1.169.0). Regenerate the hash-locked
# bundle after any bump (--universal so platform-gated transitives are pinned for
# the linux image, not just the dev host):
#   uv pip compile --generate-hashes --universal --python-version 3.12 \
#     requirements-scanners.in -o requirements-scanners.txt
semgrep==1.169.0
